==============================================================================
 XFMGR2 - an XTree-style file manager for the Commander X16    (Build 185)
==============================================================================

 A dual-pane, keyboard-driven file manager. A collapsible DIRECTORY tree on
 the left, the selected directory's FILES on the right, with file tagging, a
 banked text/hex viewer, a BMX image viewer, a whole-disk Find, and a full set
 of file operations - copy, move, rename, delete, mkdir and prune - plus edit
 via the ROM X16 Edit and switchable colour themes.

 The bottom command menu is MODIFIER-DRIVEN. By default it shows MENU (plain
 keys). Hold CTRL for the CTRL menu, hold ALT (the Commodore key) for the ALT
 menu; release to return to MENU. The plain menu is context-sensitive: the
 DIRECTORY pane and the FILE pane offer different commands.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 NAVIGATION (either pane)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Up / Dn     Move the cursor within the focused pane
   TAB         Switch focus between the DIRECTORY and FILE panes
   Right       Focus the FILE pane (logs the dir's files on the fly)
   Left        Focus the DIRECTORY pane
   F1          Show this help
   Q           Quit, leaving the shell in the LAUNCH directory

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 DIRECTORY pane (plain keys)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Enter       Log the directory if new; else expand / collapse it
   M           Make a new subdirectory in the selected folder
   R           Rename the selected directory
   D           Delete the selected folder (empty folders only)
   P           Prune - recursively delete the folder and all its contents
               (type 'prune' to confirm)
   F3          Re-log sub-folders (picks up folders made since logging)
   A           About box (version, banked-RAM usage, credits)

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 FILE pane (plain keys)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   T           Tag current file, then advance
   U           Untag current file, then advance
   V           View - .bmx in the image viewer, else the text/hex viewer
   P           Play music - .zsm (ZSound) or .wav (PCM) audio
   E           Edit file in the ROM X16 Edit, then return
   C           Copy selected (or all tagged) file(s) to a directory
   M           Move selected (or all tagged) file(s) to a directory
   R           Rename (supports * and ? wildcards)
   D           Delete current file (confirm)
   F           Set the file-spec filter (e.g. *.prg, Enter = * = all)

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 CTRL menu (acts on the current directory / all tagged)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Ctrl-T      Tag all files in this directory
   Ctrl-U      Untag all files in this directory
   Ctrl-I      Invert tags in this directory
   Ctrl-W      Tag files matching a wildcard
   Ctrl-G      ShowAll - modal list of every tagged file across all dirs
   Ctrl-F      Find files across the whole disk
               (Ctrl-N in the emulator, Ctrl-F on hardware)
   Ctrl-C      Copy all tagged files (from all dirs) to one destination
   Ctrl-M      Move all tagged files (from all dirs) to one destination
               (Ctrl-O in the emulator, Ctrl-M on hardware)
   Ctrl-X      Delete all tagged files in this directory
               (Ctrl-X in the emulator, Ctrl-D on hardware)

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 ALT menu  (ALT = the Commodore key)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Alt-S       Cycle sort order: name -> extension -> size
   Alt-X       Execute - quit XFMGR and chain-run the selected program
   Alt-Q       Quit, leaving the shell in the CURRENTLY SELECTED directory
   Alt-F3      Re-log the current context (sub-folders in DIR, files in FILE)
   Alt-F10     Open the colour-theme setup (quits to XFSETUP.PRG)

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 In text prompts (Copy, Move, Rename, Mkdir, Filespec, Tag-spec, Find)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Up          Pop up the recent-entry history for this prompt
   F2          Open the directory picker (Copy/Move destinations)
   Left/Right  Move the cursor in the field   (Home = start)
   Enter       Accept (saved to history)
   Esc         Cancel

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 In the ShowAll / Find / directory-picker modals
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Up / Dn     Move          Enter  Select / jump to the file
   +           Expand (picker, logs on demand)     - Collapse
   Esc / Q     Cancel        U      Untag the highlighted entry (ShowAll)

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 File formats the viewer handles
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Text        ANY file opens as text. Non-printable bytes show as '.'.
               Press H at any time for a raw hex dump, H again for text.
   Hex         Any file, as a hex + ASCII dump (H toggles text <-> hex).
   ZSM music   .zsm files (auto-detected) show a parsed header breakout -
               version, tick rate, loop point, PCM, FM (YM) and PSG voices.
               Press H for the raw hex bytes.
   BMX image   .bmx bitmaps do NOT open here - V sends them full-screen to
               the BMX image viewer; any key returns to the file list.

   Big files that are too large for the pager fall back to the ROM X16 Edit.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Music playback (P)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   ZSM         .zsm songs play through the zsmkit engine (FM + PSG + PCM).
               The whole song is loaded into free RAM banks, so a very large
               song may report "no free RAM banks" - close/relog to free some.
               (V on a .zsm still shows the header breakout; P plays it.)
   WAV         .wav plays uncompressed PCM: 8- or 16-bit, mono or stereo, up
               to ~48 kHz. Compressed (ADPCM) wavs are not supported yet.
   Controls    SPACE pauses / resumes; Q, ESC or STOP stops and returns.
   Needs       zsmkit.bin (ZSM) and xmusic.ovl (WAV) beside the program; if
               either is missing, P reports it and does nothing.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 In the text / hex viewer (V, and this help)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   PgDn/PgUp   Page          T  Top        B  Bottom
   H           Toggle hex / text
   F           Find a string
   N / Space    Repeat the search (find next)
   Q / Esc     Exit back to the file list

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 EMULATOR vs REAL HARDWARE  (key differences)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   XFMGR detects whether it is running under the x16emu emulator and rebinds
   the CTRL commands the emulator window grabs before they reach the app. The
   bottom CTRL menu always shows the binding that is ACTIVE right now.

     Command          Emulator     Real hardware
     Delete tagged    Ctrl-X       Ctrl-D
     Find files       Ctrl-N       Ctrl-F
     Move tagged      Ctrl-O       Ctrl-M

   Ctrl-S is also swallowed by the emulator, so Tag-by-wildcard is Ctrl-W in
   both environments. ALT is the Commodore (C=) key on a real X16; in the
   emulator it is the left Alt key. Everything else - plain keys, function
   keys, arrows - behaves identically in both.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 LIMITS
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Directories Up to 254 directories are logged per session (the tree caps
               there). Find scans the WHOLE disk no matter how many folders it
               holds, but only logs the folders that CONTAIN a match. If one
               search's matches are spread across more than 254 folders,
               logging stops there and the results are marked "(partial)".
   Find/ShowAll At most 255 matching files are collected; beyond that the list
               is marked "(partial)". Very deep folder paths may be skipped
               (also shown as "(partial)").

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 HOW IT IS INSTALLED  (folder layout)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   The installer keeps the whole app in ONE folder and drops a tiny launcher
   in the drive root, so you can start it from anywhere:

     /                     drive root
     +-- XT                one-line BASIC launcher  (LOAD "/XFMGR/XFMGR.PRG")
     +-- XFMGR/            everything else lives here
          +-- XFMGR.PRG        the main program
          +-- *.OVL            banked overlays (viewer, image, music, ui, misc)
          +-- XFSETUP.PRG      the colour-theme setup (Alt-F10)
          +-- ZSMKIT.BIN       the ZSM music engine
          +-- XFMGR.HLP        this help file
          +-- XFMGR.CFG        your saved theme (kept across updates)

   To install: Copy the unpacked release files plus INSTALL.PRG into one
   folder, boot the X16, CD into that folder and run INSTALL. It creates
   /XFMGR, copies the app files into it, and writes the root /XT launcher.
   (The install folder can be removed after the install is complete)

   To launch from *any* directory afterwards:   ^/xt
   (XFMGR itself always presents the tree rooted at "/", so you can roam the
   whole drive no matter where you started it.)

